  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Grapple</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>physical.grapple</abilityid>
    <abilityclass>Fight</abilityclass>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	Grappling involves grabbing, tackling or wrestling an opponent and holding 
	them without harming them.  Other attacks against a grappled opponent
	are hindered by the grappler being close to the opponent and the opponents
	struggling.
      </p>

      <p>
	Every round that an opponent is grappled they may make an opposed Str test 
	against their grappler to escape.  Once grappled it takes a round for 
	a second character to tie-up, or otherwise constrain, the opponent.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>

    <abilitylevels>
      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>0</levelnumber>
        <prereqabilitylevel></prereqabilitylevel>
        <defaultlore>0</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>0</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>0</defaultgeneral>
	<check>Std 2d8 + Str Modifier vs max of opponents Str or Grapple</check>
        <successes>2</successes>
        <attempts>1</attempts>
      </abilitylevel>

      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>1</levelnumber>
        <prereqabilitylevel></prereqabilitylevel>
        <defaultlore>0</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>2</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>2</defaultgeneral>
        <successes>2</successes>
        <attempts>1</attempts>
	<check>Std 2d8 + 2 + Str Modifier vs opponents Str or Grapple</check>
      </abilitylevel>
      
      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>2</levelnumber>
        <defaultlore>0</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>3</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>0</defaultgeneral>
	<check>Std 2d8 + 4 + Str Modifier vs opponents Str or Grapple</check>
      </abilitylevel>      
    </abilitylevels>
  </ability>


  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Head Butt</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>physical.head_butt</abilityid>
    <abilityclass>Fight</abilityclass>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	A head butt involves the attacker driving the top of their head into the bridge 
	of the defenders nose.  Head butting is mainly used as an attack of last resort or 
	as a surprise attack.  An attacker may only head butt someone immediately in 
	front or behind them.  An character may head butt when grappled.
      </p>

      <p>
	Head butts do +2 damage if the attacker is wearing a helmet and -2 damage
	if the defender is wearing a helmet.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>
    <abilitylevels>
      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>0</levelnumber>
